        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 7:32PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Highway 62 Near Crater Lake, or near Crater Lake, moving northwest at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thousand Springs Sno-Park and Highway 62 Near Crater Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
